woman.name: Ava
woman.mean: A Latin name meaning 'bird'. It symbolizes freedom and perspective.

woman.name: Bella
woman.mean: Of Italian origin meaning 'beautiful'. Represents beauty and charm.

woman.name: Chloe
woman.mean: Greek origin meaning 'blooming' or 'fertility'. It symbolizes new beginnings and growth.

woman.name: Daisy
woman.mean: Derived from the name of the flower, which symbolizes purity and innocence.

woman.name: Ella
woman.mean: Short form of Eleanor or Ellen, meaning 'light' or 'beautiful fairy woman'. It represents brightness and allure.

woman.name: Fiona
woman.mean: Of Gaelic origin meaning 'white' or 'fair'. Represents purity and fairness.

woman.name: Grace
woman.mean: Latin origin meaning 'graciousness' or 'charm'. It symbolizes elegance and dignity.

woman.name: Hazel
woman.mean: Named after the hazel tree; symbolizes wisdom and protection.

woman.name: Isla
woman.mean: Of Scottish origin, named after the island of Islay. It symbolizes nature and beauty.

woman.name: Julia
woman.mean: Latin for 'youthful'. It connotes youth, energy, and vitality.

woman.name: Kara
woman.mean: Means 'friend' in Turkish and 'beloved' in Italian. It symbolizes love and friendship.

woman.name: Luna
woman.mean: Latin for 'moon', representing mystery and the feminine power.

woman.name: Mia
woman.mean: Of Italian and Spanish origin meaning 'mine'. It symbolizes possession and importance.

woman.name: Nora
woman.mean: Short form of Honora or Eleanora, meaning 'honor'. It represents dignity and respect.

woman.name: Olivia
woman.mean: Derived from olive or olive tree. Symbolizes peace and fruitfulness.

woman.name: Penelope
woman.mean: Of Greek origin meaning 'weaver'. It symbolizes patience and fidelity.

woman.name: Quinn
woman.mean: Of Irish origin meaning 'wise' or 'counsel'. It symbolizes intelligence and wisdom.

woman.name: Ruby
woman.mean: Named after the red gemstone, symbolizing love and vitality.

woman.name: Sophia
woman.mean: Greek for 'wisdom'. It connotes intelligence, sophistication, and knowledge.

woman.name: Tessa
woman.mean: Short form of Theresa, meaning 'to reap', 'to gather'. It represents abundance and bounty.

woman.name: Uma
woman.mean: Of Sanskrit origin meaning 'light', 'tranquility', 'splendor'. It symbolizes peace and beauty.

woman.name: Violet
woman.mean: Named after the flower, symbolizing modesty, virtue, and affection.

woman.name: Willow
woman.mean: Named after the willow tree, symbolizing grace and flexibility.

woman.name: Xenia
woman.mean: Of Greek origin meaning 'hospitality'. It symbolizes welcoming and generosity.

woman.name: Yara
woman.mean: Of Arabic and Brazilian origin meaning 'small butterfly' and 'water lady'. It represents transformation and fluidity.

woman.name: Zoe
woman.mean: Greek for 'life'. It represents vitality and energy.

woman.name: Audrey
woman.mean: Old English origin meaning 'noble strength'. It symbolizes power and nobility.

woman.name: Brooke
woman.mean: Named after a small, natural stream. It symbolizes calmness and flow.

woman.name: Cecilia
woman.mean: Latin origin meaning 'blind'. Historically represents musical talents and saintly faith.

woman.name: Delilah
woman.mean: Of Hebrew origin meaning 'delicate'. It has connotations of allure and mystery.

woman.name: Eleanor
woman.mean: Of Greek origin meaning 'shining light' or 'sun ray'. It symbolizes brightness and leadership.

woman.name: Faith
woman.mean: English origin meaning 'trust', 'belief'. It symbolizes strong conviction and spirituality.

woman.name: Genevieve
woman.mean: Of Germanic origin meaning 'woman of the family' or 'tribe woman'. It represents heritage and strength.

woman.name: Harper
woman.mean: Originally an English surname for someone who plays the harp. It symbolizes creativity and musical talent.

woman.name: Ivy
woman.mean: Named after the ivy plant, symbolizing fidelity and eternity.

woman.name: Josephine
woman.mean: French form of Joseph, meaning 'Jehovah increases'. It symbolizes growth and prosperity.

woman.name: Kiara
woman.mean: Italian origin meaning 'clear', 'bright', 'famous'. It represents clarity and radiance.

woman.name: Leah
woman.mean: Hebrew origin meaning 'weary' but traditionally symbolizes devotion and virtue.

woman.name: Madeline
woman.mean: Of English origin, derived from Magdalene, meaning 'woman from Magdala'. It represents strength and honor.

woman.name: Natalie
woman.mean: Of Latin origin meaning 'born on Christmas'. It symbolizes joy and celebration.

woman.name: Ophelia
woman.mean: Greek origin meaning 'help'. Famous from Shakespeare's 'Hamlet', it represents sensitivity and tragic beauty.

woman.name: Piper
woman.mean: Originally an English surname for someone who played the pipes. It represents joyfulness and musicality.

woman.name: Quincy
woman.mean: Of French origin, meaning 'estate of the fifth son'. Represents inheritance and tradition.

woman.name: Rosalie
woman.mean: French origin, meaning 'rose'. Symbolizes love, beauty, and tenderness.

woman.name: Serena
woman.mean: Latin for 'calm', 'peaceful'. It represents tranquility and harmony.

woman.name: Trinity
woman.mean: Latin for 'triad'. Represents the union of mind, body, and spirit.

woman.name: Ursula
woman.mean: Latin for 'little bear'. It symbolizes strength and endurance.

woman.name: Veronica
woman.mean: Of Latin origin meaning 'true image', 'victory bringer'. It symbolizes honesty and triumph.

woman.name: Wendy
woman.mean: Invented for the book 'Peter Pan', possibly derived from Welsh meaning 'fair and blessed'. It represents youthfulness and fantasy.

woman.name: Xiomara
woman.mean: Of Spanish origin meaning 'ready for battle'. It represents strength and readiness.
